#. <section class="sutta" id="sn41.9"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn41.9:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 41"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 41"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn41.9:0.2"
msgid "1. Cittavagga"
msgstr "1. With Citta"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 9. Acelakassapasutta → acelasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn41.9:0.3"
msgid "9. Acelakassapasutta"
msgstr "9. With Kassapa, the Naked Ascetic"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.301"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn41.9:1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena acelo kassapo macchikāsaṇḍaṃ anuppatto hoti cittassa "
"gahapatino purāṇagihisahāyo."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the naked ascetic Kassapa, who in lay life was an old "
"friend of Citta, had arrived at Macchikāsaṇḍa."

msgctxt "sn41.9:1.2"
msgid ""
"Assosi kho citto gahapati: “acelo kira kassapo macchikāsaṇḍaṃ anuppatto "
"amhākaṃ purāṇagihisahāyo”ti."
msgstr "Citta the householder heard that he had arrived."

msgctxt "sn41.9:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho citto gahapati yena acelo kassapo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"acelena kassapena saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr "So he went up to him, and they exchanged greetings."

msgctxt "sn41.9:1.4"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho citto gahapati acelaṃ kassapaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to the naked ascetic Kassapa:"

msgctxt "sn41.9:1.5"
msgid "“kīvaciraṃ pabbajitassa, bhante kassapā”ti?"
msgstr "“Sir, Kassapa, how long has it been since you went forth?”"

msgctxt "sn41.9:1.6"
msgid "“Tiṃsamattāni kho me, gahapati, vassāni pabbajitassā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s been thirty years, householder.”"

#. VAR: uttari manussadhammā → uttarimanussadhammo (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn41.9:1.7"
msgid ""
"“Imehi pana te, bhante, tiṃsamattehi vassehi atthi koci uttari manussadhammā "
"alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso adhigato phāsuvihāro”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But sir, in these thirty years have you achieved any superhuman distinction "
"in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones, a meditation at ease?”"

# https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/did-naked-ascetics-spank-each-others-bottoms/3056
msgctxt "sn41.9:1.8"
msgid ""
"“Imehi kho me, gahapati, tiṃsamattehi vassehi pabbajitassa natthi koci "
"uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso adhigato phāsuvihāro, "
"aññatra naggeyyā ca muṇḍeyyā ca pāvaḷanipphoṭanāya cā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“I have no such achievement, householder, only nakedness, baldness, and "
"pokes in the buttocks.”"

msgctxt "sn41.9:1.9"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, citto gahapati acelaṃ kassapaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Citta said to him:"

msgctxt "sn41.9:1.10"
msgid "“acchariyaṃ vata, bho, abbhutaṃ vata, bho."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, it’s amazing,"

#. VAR: svākkhātatā → svākhyātatā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn41.9:1.11"
msgid ""
"Dhammassa svākkhātatā yatra hi nāma tiṃsamattehi vassehi na koci uttari "
"manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso adhigato abhavissa phāsuvihāro, "
"aññatra naggeyyā ca muṇḍeyyā ca pāvaḷanipphoṭanāya cā”ti."
msgstr ""
"how well explained the teaching is. For in thirty years you have achieved no "
"superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones, no "
"meditation at ease, only nakedness, baldness, and pokes in the buttocks.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.302"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn41.9:2.1"
msgid "“Tuyhaṃ pana, gahapati, kīvaciraṃ upāsakattaṃ upagatassā”ti?"
msgstr "“But householder, how long have you been a lay follower?”"

msgctxt "sn41.9:2.2"
msgid ""
"“Mayhampi kho pana, bhante, tiṃsamattāni vassāni upāsakattaṃ upagatassā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s been thirty years, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn41.9:2.3"
msgid ""
"“Imehi pana te, gahapati, tiṃsamattehi vassehi atthi koci uttari "
"manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso adhigato phāsuvihāro”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But householder, in these thirty years have you achieved any superhuman "
"distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones, a meditation "
"at ease?”"

# Following BB’s reading kim hi no siya based on Se. See however my comment on kathanhi no siya at SN 22.1
msgctxt "sn41.9:2.4"
msgid "“Gihinopi siyā, bhante."
msgstr "“How, sir, could I not?"

msgctxt "sn41.9:2.5"
msgid ""
"Ahañhi, bhante, yāvadeva ākaṅkhāmi, vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi "
"dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharāmi."
msgstr ""
"For whenever I want, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from "
"unskillful qualities, I enter and remain in the first absorption, which has "
"the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping "
"it connected."

# punctuation in MS has been corrected, ellipsis is added.
msgctxt "sn41.9:2.6"
msgid ""
"Ahañhi, bhante, yāvadeva ākaṅkhāmi, vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … dutiyaṃ "
"jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāmi."
msgstr ""
"And whenever I want, as the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are "
"stilled … I enter and remain in the second absorption."

msgctxt "sn41.9:2.7"
msgid ""
"Ahañhi, bhante, yāvadeva ākaṅkhāmi, pītiyā ca virāgā … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ "
"upasampajja viharāmi."
msgstr ""
"And whenever I want, with the fading away of rapture … I enter and remain in "
"the third absorption."

msgctxt "sn41.9:2.8"
msgid ""
"Ahañhi, bhante, yāvadeva ākaṅkhāmi, sukhassa ca pahānā … pe … catutthaṃ "
"jhānaṃ upasampajja viharāmi."
msgstr ""
"And whenever I want, giving up pleasure and pain … I enter and remain in the "
"fourth absorption."

#. VAR: bhagavato → bhagavatā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn41.9:2.9"
msgid ""
"Sace kho panāhaṃ, bhante, bhagavato paṭhamataraṃ kālaṃ kareyyaṃ, "
"anacchariyaṃ kho panetaṃ yaṃ maṃ bhagavā evaṃ byākareyya:"
msgstr ""
"If I pass away before the Buddha, it wouldn’t be surprising if the Buddha "
"declares of me:"

msgctxt "sn41.9:2.10"
msgid ""
"‘natthi taṃ saṃyojanaṃ yena saṃyojanena saṃyutto citto gahapati puna imaṃ "
"lokaṃ āgaccheyyā’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The householder Citta is bound by no fetter that might return him to this "
"world.’”"

msgctxt "sn41.9:2.11"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, acelo kassapo cittaṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When this was said, Kassapa said to Citta:"

msgctxt "sn41.9:2.12"
msgid "“acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, it’s amazing,"

#. VAR: gihī odātavasano → gihī odātavasanā (bj)
#. VAR: adhigamissati → adhigamissanti (bj)
msgctxt "sn41.9:2.13"
msgid ""
"Dhammassa svākkhātatā, yatra hi nāma gihī odātavasano evarūpaṃ uttari "
"manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ adhigamissati phāsuvihāraṃ."
msgstr ""
"how well explained the teaching is. For a white-clothed layperson can "
"achieve such a superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the "
"noble ones, a meditation at ease."

msgctxt "sn41.9:2.14"
msgid ""
"Labheyyāhaṃ, gahapati, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye pabbajjaṃ, labheyyaṃ "
"upasampadan”ti."
msgstr ""
"Sir, may I receive the going forth, the ordination in the Buddha’s presence?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn41.9:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho citto gahapati acelaṃ kassapaṃ ādāya yena therā bhikkhū "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā there bhikkhū etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Citta the householder took the naked ascetic Kassapa to see the senior "
"mendicants, and said to them:"

msgctxt "sn41.9:3.2"
msgid "“ayaṃ, bhante, acelo kassapo amhākaṃ purāṇagihisahāyo."
msgstr ""
"“Sirs, this is the naked ascetic Kassapa, who in lay life was an old friend "
"of mine."

msgctxt "sn41.9:3.3"
msgid "Imaṃ therā pabbājentu upasampādentu."
msgstr "May the senior monks give him the going forth, the ordination."

msgctxt "sn41.9:3.4"
msgid ""
"Ahamassa ussukkaṃ karissāmi "
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānan”ti."
msgstr ""
"I’ll make sure that he’s provided with robes, alms-food, lodgings, and "
"medicines and supplies for the sick.”"

msgctxt "sn41.9:3.5"
msgid ""
"Alattha kho acelo kassapo imasmiṃ dhammavinaye pabbajjaṃ, alattha "
"upasampadaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And the naked ascetic Kassapa received the going forth, the ordination in "
"this teaching and training."

msgctxt "sn41.9:3.6"
msgid ""
"Acirūpasampanno ca panāyasmā kassapo eko vūpakaṭṭho appamatto ātāpī "
"pahitatto viharanto nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā "
"anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme "
"sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsi."
msgstr ""
"Not long after his ordination, Venerable Kassapa, living alone, withdrawn, "
"diligent, keen, and resolute, soon realized the supreme end of the spiritual "
"path in this very life. He lived having achieved with his own insight the "
"goal for which people from good families rightly go forth from the lay life "
"to homelessness."

msgctxt "sn41.9:3.7"
msgid ""
"“Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā”ti "
"abbhaññāsi."
msgstr ""
"He understood: “Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; "
"what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of "
"existence.”"

msgctxt "sn41.9:3.8"
msgid "Aññataro ca panāyasmā kassapo arahataṃ ahosīti."
msgstr "And Venerable Kassapa became one of the perfected."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn41.9:3.9"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
